communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This is the 1st notification of RVF from Kenya's coastal Kilifi County, situated south of the RVF-infected Tana River County, in south east Kenya.

Kilifi was one of the 20 counties advised during the 2nd week of June 2018 [week of 11 Jun 2018], shortly after the initial detection of human RVF cases in Kenya, "to immediately commence animal vaccination and vector control." The other 19 were Uasin Gishu, Trans Nzoia, Nakuru, Laikipia, Kajiado, Baringo, Wajir, Garissa, Marsabit, Meru, Machakos, Taita Taveta, Tana River, Mombasa, Kwale, Nyeri, Tharaka Nithi, Murang'a, and Kiambu (see 4th item in archive no. 20180615.5858590).

The total number of reported RVF outbreaks in Kenya's animals since the start of the event (3 Jun 2018) is 10, according to the 6 official reports submitted so far to the OIE. The most recent follow-up report was submitted on Mon 6 Aug 2018, informing the absence of new outbreaks (since 2 Jul 2018). The outbreaks were reported from the following counties (number of outbreaks in brackets): Mandera (1), Wajir (2), Marsabit (1), Isiolo (2), Meru (1), Baringo (1), Tara River (1), and Siaya (1). Links to all reports and a map presenting their locations are available at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?fupser=&dothis=&reportid=26827.

According to recent media reports, the counties of Kajiado and, currently, Kilifi should be added to the list of counties in which RVF has been recorded in animals. For Kenya's counties map, see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Counties_of_Kenya.

The 1st OIE notification of RVF from another Eastern African country, namely Rwanda, is being published separately (see Rift Valley fever - Eastern Africa (26): Rwanda, bovine, OIE 20180811.5959586). - Mod.AS

HealthMap/ProMED-mail map: Kilifi District, Coast, Kenya: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5959420,3927.]
